---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">June 26, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Launched <a href="/compare/dogbreederpro-alternative" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/dogbreederpro-alternative</a> — the C3 page in the 12-page LP cluster plan, pivoted from the originally specified BreedTools page after pre-flight verification found BreedTools is a free-tools-and-calculators site (no signup, no subscription), not a competing SaaS breeder management platform. The brief&apos;s footnote explicitly allowed this pivot; Dog Breeder Pro is a real subscription SaaS already named on <a href="/compare/best-dog-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/best-dog-breeding-software</a>.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">New file</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
    <li><code>src/pages/compare/dogbreederpro-alternative.astro</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Sections</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
    <li>Hero with H1 &quot;Looking for a Dog Breeder Pro Alternative? An Honest Comparison&quot; + verified-date line + dual CTA (14-day free trial / pricing)</li>
    <li>TL;DR aside framed as &quot;pick Dog Breeder Pro if&quot; / &quot;pick BreederHQ if&quot;</li>
    <li>Side-by-side comparison table — 9 rows including price, trial length, species, marketplace, buyer pipeline, breeding-decision tools, languages (8 vs EN-only), mobile, last verified</li>
    <li>Where Dog Breeder Pro is genuinely strong (4 honest wins, including multi-language and focused dogs-only scope)</li>
    <li>Where BreederHQ is different (6 capability differences, all sourced to public materials)</li>
    <li>Pricing detail cards (Dog Breeder Pro $8.49/mo Standard, $14.99/mo Premium, 30-day trial / BreederHQ pricing page + FOUNDER50)</li>
    <li>&quot;What this page is not&quot; — honesty note + trust posture pointer to <a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a></li>
    <li>Final CTA + non-affiliation disclaimer</li>
    <li>7-question FAQ (multi-species scenario, marketplace vs public dog page, data migration, trial length)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">SEO targeting</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
    <li>Primary query: <em>dog breeder pro alternative</em></li>
    <li>Secondary queries: <em>dogbreederpro alternative</em>, <em>dog breeder pro vs</em>, <em>alternative to dog breeder pro</em>, <em>dogbreederpro vs breederhq</em></li>
    <li>Article + FAQPage JSON-LD (page-scoped Article schema in the page; FAQPage emitted by BaseLayout via the <code>faqs</code> prop)</li>
    <li>Anti-cannibalization: H1 contains the word &quot;alternative&quot; — does not compete with <a href="/compare/best-dog-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/best-dog-breeding-software</a> on &quot;best ... software&quot; head terms</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Internal links out</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-3 space-y-1">
    <li><a href="/pricing" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/pricing</a> (primary CTA, multiple references)</li>
    <li><a href="/compare/best-dog-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/best-dog-breeding-software</a> (deeper buyer&apos;s guide)</li>
    <li><a href="/breeder-management-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/breeder-management-software</a> (Cluster A anchor, in final CTA)</li>
    <li><a href="/trust" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/trust</a> (honesty/trust posture)</li>
    <li><a href="/" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/</a> (breadcrumb + header)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Trust posture</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700">Honest-comparison voice throughout. Every Dog Breeder Pro claim is sourced to dogbreederpro.com (pricing page + features page) and dated. Where Dog Breeder Pro wins (lower entry price, longer trial, 8-language support, focused dogs-only scope), the page says so explicitly. No screenshots of the competitor, no inferred customer counts, no &quot;we heard from customers&quot; claims. Page includes the standard BreederHQ trust-posture pointer: we do not verify, vet, or vouch.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Ads campaign dependency</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700">The Campaign B (conquesting) CSV currently points Ad Group B3 at <code>/compare/breedtools-alternative</code>. That ad group must be paused until the AG-B3 keywords, RSAs, and final URL are swapped to Dog Breeder Pro variants (<em>dog breeder pro alternative</em>, <em>dogbreederpro vs</em>, etc.). The watch-checklist already includes a Day 0 gate that catches this: ad groups whose LP is not shipped stay paused.</p>
</article>
